k/blair-castle-interior-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","kid-friendly","photogenic"]},{"name":"Scone Palace","county":"Perth and Kinross","type":"palace","condition":"intact","era":"19th century","rating":4.3,"reviewCount":2670,"access":"paid","description":"Built on the site where Scottish kings were crowned on the Stone of Scone for centuries. The current Gothic palace houses an outstanding collection of porcelain, furniture, and ivories.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Scone_Palace_-_Front_side.jpg/500px-Scone_Palace_-_Front_side.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/scone-palace-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scone-palace-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scone-palace-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scone-palace-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","kid-friendly","hidden-gem"]},{"name":"Dunfermline Abbey","county":"Fife","type":"abbey","condition":"partial ruin","era":"12th century","rating":4.4,"reviewCount":2340,"access":"free","description":"The burial place of Robert the Bruce and many Scottish monarchs, Dunfermline was Scotland's capital in the medieval period. The Romanesque nave columns are powerful.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Dunfermline_Abbey_Geograph.jpg/500px-Dunfermline_Abbey_Geograph.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/dunfermline-abbey-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunfermline-abbey-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunfermline-abbey-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/dunfermline-abbey-5.jpg"],"tags":["dramatic-ruin","photogenic","hidden-gem"]},{"name":"Ravenscraig Castle","county":"Fife","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"15th century","rating":3.9,"reviewCount":780,"access":"free","description":"One of the first castles in Britain designed to withstand cannon fire, Ravenscraig's thick-walled towers were built for James II in 1460. It overlooks Kirkcaldy's beach.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/View_of_Antrim_Cas