 and Kinross","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"15th-16th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":95,"access":"free","description":"A compact 15th-century tower house near Milnathort in Kinross-shire, with an unusual corner tower and rooftop caphouse. Quietly impressive Lowland Scottish fortification.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/BurleighCastle.jpg/500px-BurleighCastle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/burleigh-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/burleigh-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/burleigh-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/burleigh-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","free-entry","medieval"]},{"name":"Methven Castle","county":"Perth and Kinross","type":"castle","condition":"partial ruin","era":"17th century","rating":3.4,"reviewCount":55,"access":"exterior-only","description":"A substantial 17th-century castle in Perthshire, site of the Battle of Methven where Bruce was defeated. Now a private residence in rolling agricultural land.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5f/Methven_Castle.jpg/500px-Methven_Castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/wiki-methven-castle.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","medieval"]},{"name":"Castle Menzies","county":"Perth and Kinross","type":"castle","condition":"restored","era":"16th century","rating":3.9,"reviewCount":580,"access":"paid","description":"A magnificent 16th-century Z-plan castle in Highland Perthshire, magnificently restored by the Menzies Clan Society. Bonnie Prince Charlie slept here — and his room is still shown.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/castle-menzies.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/castle-menzies-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/castle-menzies-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/castle-menzies-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/castle-menzies-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","guided-tours","museum","gift-shop","atmospheric","medieval"]},{"name":"Grandtully Castle","county":"Perth and Kinross","type":"tower house","condition":"intact","era":"15th century","rating":3.4,"reviewCount":55,"access":"exterior-only","description":"A tower house overlooking the Tay valley in Perthshire, notable for its nearby church with astonishing painted timber ceiling — a hidden masterpiece of Scottish art.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/Grandtully_Castle_%28geograph_3890325%29.jpg/500px-Grandtully_Castle_%28geograph_3890325%29.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/wiki-grandtully-castle.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","medieval","atmospheric"]},{"name":"Megginch Castle","county":"Perth and Kinross","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"15th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":80,"access":"paid","description":"A 15th-century tower house in the Carse of Gowrie, home to the Drummonds for over 500 years. Famous for its ancient gardens, topiary, and a 1,000-year-old yew tree.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/megginch-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/wiki-megginch-castle.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","gardens","events-venue","filming-location","atmospheric"]},{"name":"Balhousie Castle","county":"Perth and Kinross","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"15th century","rating":3.9,"reviewCount":650,"access":"paid","description":"A 15th-century castle in Perth, now home to the Black Watch Museum — showcasing 350 years of Scotland's most famous regiment. Military heritage in baronial splendour.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Perth_and_Kinross_Perth_Balhousie_Castle_1.jpg/500px-Perth_and_Kinross_Perth_Balhousie_Castle_1.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/balhousie-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balhousie-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balhousie-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balhousie-castle-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","museum","gift-shop","kid-friendly","tearoom-cafe"]},{"name":"Kellie Castle","county":"Fife","type":"castle","condition":"intact","era":"12th-17th century","rating":4.1,"reviewCount":1200,"access":"paid","description":"A romantic Scottish castle with roots reaching back to 1150, wrapped in walled gardens and steeped in centuries of aristocratic intrigue — from medieval earls to Victorian artists who saved it from ruin.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/kellie-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","gardens","romantic","photogenic","atmospheric","medieval","guided-tours"]},{"name":"Scotstarvit Tower","county":"Fife","type":"tower house","condition":"intact","era":"16th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":120,"access":"free","description":"A perfectly preserved six-storey tower house rising from the Fife hills — home to a satirist who skewered Scottish statesmen from his lofty perch.","image":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/76/Scotstarvit_Tower.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/scotstarvit-tower-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["well-preserved","hilltop","photogenic","medieval","guided-tours"]},{"name":"Macduff's Castle","county":"Fife","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"14th-16th century","rating":3.4,"reviewCount":65,"access":"exterior-only","description":"A Shakespearean ruin above the Wemyss Caves — where the legendary Thane of Fife's descendants held court and Edward I once slept before betraying his host.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/macduff-s-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","coastal","dark-brooding","medieval","atmospheric"]},{"name":"Balwearie Castle","county":"Fife","type":"tower house","condition":"ruin","era":"15th century","rating":3.2,"reviewCount":30,"access":"free","description":"A ruined tower house near Kirkcaldy in Fife, once the seat of the Scott family. Standing quietly in suburbia, a medieval survivor in an unlikely setting.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-5.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-main-2.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-main-3.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-main-4.jpg","https://img.castlecore.uk/balwearie-castle-main-5.jpg"],"tags":["ruins-romantic","medieval","free-entry"]},{"name":"Newark Castle (Fife)","county":"Fife","type":"castle","condition":"ruin","era":"15th century","rating":3.5,"reviewCount":95,"access":"free","description":"Ruined 15th-century castle on the Fife coast near St Monans, overlooking the Firth of Forth. Not to be confused with its better-known Port Glasgow namesake.","image":"https://img.castlecore.uk/newark-castle-fife.jpg","gallery":["https://img.castleco